```r
# Detect the \.git\ folder. This will be in the project root directory.
# Use this as the root directory to ensure proper sourcing of functions
# no matter where this is called from.
root_dir <- rprojroot::find_root(rprojroot::has_dir(\.git\))
scratch_dir <- file.path(root_dir, \scratch\)
analysis_dir <- file.path(root_dir, \analyses\, \tmb-vaf-longitudinal\) 
input_dir <- file.path(analysis_dir, \input\)

# Input files
tmb_autopsy_file <- file.path(scratch_dir, \tmb_autopsy.tsv\)

# File path to plots directory
plots_dir <-
  file.path(analysis_dir, \plots\)
if (!dir.exists(plots_dir)) {
  dir.create(plots_dir)
}

source(paste0(analysis_dir, \/util/function-create-stacked-barplot.R\))
source(paste0(analysis_dir, \/util/function-create-barplot.R\))
source(paste0(root_dir, \/figures/theme.R\))

# Exclude 2 samples with high number of mutations to make plot more readable
# We will exclude PT_3CHB9PK5 - Diagnosis model AND PT_6N825561 - Progessive model
  # This is because the samples contain > 13000 and >2000 mutations, respectively
  # making it hard to adjust y axis and read the plot
tmb_autopsy_filter <- tmb_autopsy %>%
    filter(!Kids_First_Participant_ID %in% c(\PT_3CHB9PK5\, \PT_6N825561\))
fname_exclude <- paste0(plots_dir, \/\, \TMB-stacked-barplot-All-Samples-exclude.pdf\)
print(fname_exclude)

Since we have multiple biospecimen samples per timepoint and patient case, let's plot these separetely.

samples <- unique(as.character(tmb_autopsy$Kids_First_Participant_ID))
print(samples)
 [1] "PT_1H2REHT2" "PT_23NZGSRJ" "PT_37B5JRP1" "PT_3CHB9PK5" "PT_3KM9W8S8" "PT_6N825561" "PT_8GN3TQRM" "PT_CXT81GRM" "PT_DNAJYFZT"
[10] "PT_HFQNKP5X" "PT_HJMP6PH2" "PT_KBFM551M" "PT_KTRJ8TFY" "PT_KZ56XHJT" "PT_MDWPRDBT" "PT_MNSEJCDM" "PT_PR4YBBH3" "PT_RJ1TJ2KH"
[19] "PT_Z4BF2NSB"
samples_include <- samples[!samples %in% c("PT_3CHB9PK5", "PT_6N825561")]

for (i in seq_along(samples_include)) {
  print(i)
  tmb_sub <- tmb_autopsy %>%
    filter(Kids_First_Participant_ID == samples_include[i])
  ylim = 100 # to scale yaxis
  
  # Run function
  fname <- paste0(plots_dir, "/", samples_include[i], "-TMB-barplot.pdf")
  print(fname)
  p <- create_barplot_sample(tmb = tmb_sub,
                             sid = samples_include[i],
                             ylim = ylim)
  pdf(file = fname, width = 5, height = 4)
  print(p)
  dev.off()
}
